{
  "name": "it-outsourcing-584848",
  "title": "Mid-Market Must Flex More Muscle in IT Outsourcing",
  "description": "Aberdeen Market Segment report analyzing IT outsourcing practices at mid-size enterprises versus Best in Class organizations. Key finding: 25% of mid-market respondents admitted their companies have not been successful with IT outsourcing; none of the Best in Class cited lack of success. Report analyzes four stages prone to planning errors: creation of quantitative business case, contract pricing negotiations, governance, and ongoing operational management. Best in Class outperform mid-market across all four stages. Three recommendations: (1) Get the RFP right \u2014 know requirements, costs, and desired advantages; (2) Don't be afraid to look outside for help \u2014 use independent consultants and legal assistance; (3) Improve relationship management \u2014 dedicate management time and hold one person accountable for the outsourcing relationship.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-05-05",
